features.additionalInfo: Enjoy secure Online Business Banking at your fingertips. As a customer on this account you may also be entitled to apply for our Online Business Banking service. If you apply for that service you will be provided with a separate Product Disclosure Statement and your use of the service will be a matter of separate agreement with us. Separate fees are applicable for this service.

We will send you a confirmation letter when you open and renew your term deposit. For term deposits with a term of six months or more, we will give you an account statement every six months. We will also send you a term deposit reinvestment notice before it matures, not only as a reminder but to also explain what you can do next.

Changes aimed at strengthening the banking system mean we need 31 days' notice if you want to withdraw your funds before the maturity date. This can also affect the interest we pay you. You can still access your money at maturity and during the grace period. You may request the withdrawal of all or part of your funds prior to the maturity date provided that you give 31 days' notice. If your Term Deposit has less than 31 days to maturity, you will only be able to access funds on the maturity date. The notice period starts on the day you request withdrawal. If you are experiencing hardship and need your funds before maturity, please contact us. If you withdraw all or part of your funds prior to the maturity date, your entitlement to interest in respect of the deposit will be reduced, according to when an early repayment is made. Please refer to the Term Deposits Terms & Conditions for further details.
For deposits which have a term of 12 months or greater, you may ask us when you lodge or renew your deposit to pay your interest monthly, quarterly, six monthly or annually.
You may ask us to pay your interest by crediting it to your Linked Account.
You may ask us to pay your interest by adding it to the balance of your Account at maturity if the term is less than 12 months.

At the end of your term, unless we notify you that we will not be renewing your deposit, you have seven calendar days (known as your 'grace period') to let us know you want to withdraw your funds or reinvest them. If you don't let us know, your funds will be automatically reinvested for the same term at the applicable rate.
You may instruct us at any time during the term of your deposit, to renew it at its maturity.
Set up and manage your term deposit online.
Your opening deposit must be made by Linked Account Transfer and must be made in Australian Dollars.

constraints.additionalInfo: To open your account, you'll need to make an opening deposit for the total amount from your linked transaction account.

eligibility.additionalInfo: Your business type is a sole trader, partnership, company, trust, super fund (including self managed super fund), society, strata or cooperative.
The business was established and has tax residency in Australia.
Maximum term of the deposit is five years.
Minimum term of the deposit is 7 days.

You must have a current Direct Debit Request at all times (this enables us to transfer funds from your Linked Account to your account). Your linked Account must be in exactly the same name as your Business TD Direct. A Bankwest Business TeleNet Saver Account cannot be used as a Linked Account.

data.name: Business TD Direct
data.description: A business term deposit with a fixed rate for a term that suits your needs. It's available to sole traders, partnerships, companies, trusts, super funds (including SMSFs), societies, strata and cooperatives that were established and have tax residency in Australia.
